WEBVTT

00:00.917 --> 00:02.551
<i>Previously on:</i>

00:02.795 --> 00:05.504
It's spring break this week,
so Zoey and her daughter

00:05.529 --> 00:06.366
are going to stay here.

00:06.367 --> 00:08.395
I'm going to need you
to move out for the week.

00:09.087 --> 00:09.985
Where you staying?

00:10.010 --> 00:11.021
I'm just going to have
to stay with Lindsey.

00:11.022 --> 00:13.490
There's someone
in the house. Go look.

00:16.043 --> 00:17.460
Ow!
What?!

00:17.462 --> 00:19.129
I'm sorry!

00:19.131 --> 00:21.664
No, no, don't touch it!

00:22.633 --> 00:24.033
I'm bored.

00:24.035 --> 00:26.536
♪ ♪

00:30.691 --> 00:33.626
I can't do this, Berta.
It's just too much.

00:33.628 --> 00:35.128
She just never stops.

00:35.130 --> 00:38.314
So, how are things going living
with Zoey and her daughter?

00:38.316 --> 00:39.516
It's good. It's good.

00:39.518 --> 00:40.733
Oh.

00:40.735 --> 00:42.468
How's living with Lyndsey?

00:42.470 --> 00:45.071
Oh, it's terrific.
That's great.

00:45.073 --> 00:47.991
So, if I could get rid of them...
Yes, 100 times yes.

00:48.609 --> 00:52.996
<i>Men...</i>

00:52.998 --> 00:54.480
Okay.

00:55.649 --> 00:57.817
Zoey...

00:57.819 --> 00:59.752
you know I love you, and...

00:59.754 --> 01:02.338
I want to live with you forever.

01:02.340 --> 01:04.040
But we got to lose the kid.

01:07.011 --> 01:09.596
- Yeah, probably not.
-  Okay.

01:09.598 --> 01:12.832
Hey, have you ever thought
of Swiss boarding schools?

01:14.351 --> 01:16.002
Hi!
Sh...

01:16.004 --> 01:17.554
She's out like a light.

01:17.556 --> 01:21.674
Really? How?
Did you drug her?

01:21.676 --> 01:24.777
I didn't think
we were allowed to drug her.

01:24.779 --> 01:27.197
She's worn out
from playing with you all day.

01:27.199 --> 01:29.115
She's not the only one.

01:29.117 --> 01:32.902
Listen...

01:32.904 --> 01:34.037
I've been thinking about this

01:34.039 --> 01:37.690
whole "moving in together"
thing.

01:37.692 --> 01:40.877
It's all right.
I admit, I had my doubts.

01:40.879 --> 01:43.746
But you have been
so wonderful with her.

01:43.748 --> 01:45.582
Thank you.

01:45.584 --> 01:48.168
This little girl
loves you so much.

01:48.170 --> 01:49.552
Really...

01:49.554 --> 01:51.638
You're all she talks about.

01:51.640 --> 01:54.090
The sun rises and sets with you.

01:54.092 --> 01:56.576
Huh...

01:58.229 --> 01:59.829
Look at what she made for you.

02:03.184 --> 02:06.219
Wow...

02:06.221 --> 02:08.854
So, you win.
We're all yours.

02:08.857 --> 02:09.906
I mean,

02:09.907 --> 02:11.491
there's a million details
to figure out

02:11.493 --> 02:13.042
before we can move in
permanently.

02:13.044 --> 02:15.128
First and foremost, where she's
going to go to school.

02:15.130 --> 02:17.797
Have you ever considered
Switzerland?

02:17.799 --> 02:19.699
You're kidding, right?

02:19.701 --> 02:22.735
I'm ki.. of course!

02:22.737 --> 02:25.872
Why would I want her
so far away?

02:25.874 --> 02:29.008
Let me put her up to bed.
Then we can start making plans.

02:29.010 --> 02:30.243
Great.

02:30.245 --> 02:31.678
Mommy?
Hmm?

02:31.680 --> 02:32.762
Where's Walden?

02:32.764 --> 02:34.264
Oh, I'm right here.

02:34.266 --> 02:36.683
I love you, Walden.

02:37.635 --> 02:39.886
I love you...

02:45.859 --> 02:48.361
Just like I planned it.

02:53.367 --> 02:55.151
Hey, roomie!

02:55.153 --> 02:57.036
You got here quick.

02:57.038 --> 02:58.955
Yeah, Lyndsey asked me
to fix the garbage disposal

02:58.957 --> 03:01.774
and I didn't like the odds.

03:01.776 --> 03:03.609
So, uh, did you talk
to Zoey yet?

03:03.611 --> 03:04.877
Yes, I did.

03:04.879 --> 03:05.628
How'd she take it?

03:05.630 --> 03:07.413
Well, I... yeah, let's...

03:07.415 --> 03:09.282
Did she cry?

03:09.284 --> 03:10.950
No...
Yelling?

03:10.952 --> 03:12.669
No. There was no yelling.

03:12.671 --> 03:16.005
Yeah, I know that I said
that I wanted to get rid of her

03:16.007 --> 03:17.590
and have you come back...

03:17.592 --> 03:19.058
Oh, no!

03:19.060 --> 03:21.060
You know, I, I love her.

03:21.062 --> 03:22.478
Oh, no!

03:22.480 --> 03:24.264
And I, I love the kid.

03:24.266 --> 03:25.481
No!

03:25.483 --> 03:27.183
I'm just going
to have to make it work.

03:27.185 --> 03:28.985
No, no, no, no, no, no!

03:28.987 --> 03:31.470
Alan, I'm sorry.

03:32.990 --> 03:36.025
Okay, okay, I'll...
I'll figure something out.

03:36.027 --> 03:39.162
If nothing else,
I am a survivor.

03:46.705 --> 03:49.005
Okay, very funny.
Survivor, I get it.

03:51.042 --> 03:54.294
Oh, come on!
I feel bad enough already.

03:54.296 --> 03:55.928
Help me...

03:55.930 --> 03:57.130
911!

03:57.132 --> 03:58.631
Oh, okay. I'll play along.

03:58.633 --> 04:01.301
Here, would 100 dollars

04:01.303 --> 04:02.769
make you better?

04:03.554 --> 04:05.004
You're not kidding?

04:05.006 --> 04:06.472
Not kidding...

04:06.474 --> 04:08.107
Don't die.

